        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hello, I've tried to delete all the entries of a db table, and according to sql commands if the \"where\" is not setted, all is removed. \r\nBut in Zend, if I do a $dbTable->delete() it asks for a \"where\" parameter. But in the parent class, \"Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract\", this parameter is optional, so I have to use \"@$dbTable->delete()\" to do that. I think this parameter should be optional in the other \"Zend_Db_Table_Abstract\", right?\r\nWe are using the trunk version. Thanks!"
        },
