        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49771",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not sure about the backwards-compatibility issues around changing Zend_Db_Table_Abstract::delete to empty the table if no parameters are given.  I workaround for this could be:\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/ See: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.db.table.html#zend.db.table.delete\r\n\/\/ See: http:\/\/zend-framework-community.634137.n4.nabble.com\/Delete-all-the-rows-of-a-table-tp657469p657472.html\r\n$table = new Bugs();\r\n$table->delete('1');\r\n{code}\r\nI'm not sure if this is completely portable across all RDBMSes supported by Zend_Db. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-02-25T16:48:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-02-25T16:49:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49772",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've attached a patch which implements your suggestion...just in case the CR Team deems your request a valid one for ZFv1.12",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-02-25T16:56:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-02-25T16:56:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50008",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Do we really want to give people the ability to delete their entire table with a single API call?  I'd opt for keeping the current signature as at least, if they really want to delete the whole table, they have to do something like $table->delete(new Zend_Db_Expr('1 = 1')); (not sure if that actually works).  Reason being, is that if somehow they coded: $table->delete($someSpec), and spec turns out to be empty, then everything is gone.\r\n\r\nI'd have to check the internals, but suggesting that where is optional seems dangerous.\r\n\r\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-12T17:25:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-12T17:25:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50033",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Ralph:  Valid point.  The OP was also arguing for consistency, as {{Zend_Db_Adapter::delete}} allows an empty where condition\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/ If $param is empty, delete all rows in the table\r\n$table->getAdapter()->delete('table', $param);\r\n{code}\r\nAt any rate, it's a trivial issue with a simple workaround, so I don't think it's necessary to pursue it. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-13T23:43:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-13T23:43:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50628",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as Won't Fix.  There is a chance that this change could break backwards-compatibility (a logic error resulting in an empty where clause would currently just emit an erorr, but after patch is applied it would empty the table).  As well, an easy-to-use and commonly known workaround exists. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-12T11:59:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-12T11:59:38.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
